   876→// defaultGitRetrier returns a default retrier configuration for Git operations.
   877→//
   878→// Retry attempts will happen when:
   879→//   - Network errors occur: connection timeouts, temporary network failures, or connection errors
   880→//   - HTTP 5xx server errors: For GET and DELETE operations (idempotent)
   881→//   - HTTP 429 Too Many Requests: For all operations (rate limiting is temporary)
   882→//
   883→// The retry behavior:
   884→//   - Total attempts: 8 (1 initial attempt + 7 retries)
   885→//   - Initial delay: 100ms before the first retry
   886→//   - Exponential backoff: delay doubles after each failed attempt (100ms → 200ms → 400ms → 800ms → 1.6s → 3.2s → 5s)
   887→//   - Maximum delay: capped at 5 seconds
   888→//   - Jitter: enabled to prevent thundering herd problems
   889→//   - Total retry window: approximately 10 seconds from first attempt to last retry
   890→//
   891→// All attempts will fail when:
   892→//   - The Git server is completely unavailable or unreachable
   893→//   - Network connectivity issues persist beyond the retry window (~10 seconds)
   894→//   - The server returns transient errors consistently for the entire retry duration
   895→//   - Context cancellation occurs before retries complete
   896→//
   897→// Non-transient errors (e.g., 4xx client errors except 429, authentication failures) are not retried and returned immediately.
   898→func defaultGitRetrier() *retry.ExponentialBackoffRetrier {
